///
=============================================================================
LLVM IR Generator — Stage 5 of the Seen Compiler Pipeline
=============================================================================

Converts the typed AST (ProgramNode) into LLVM IR text (.ll files).
This is the final stage before LLVM's own optimization and machine code
generation (opt -> llc -> clang link, or ThinLTO pipeline).

Generation follows a three-pass architecture:
  Pass 1 — registerDeclarations(): collect all function signatures, struct
           layouts, enum variants, and cross-module declares without
           generating any IR. Populates the registries that Pass 2/3 need.
  Pass 2 — emitClassType() + emitPrologue(): emit LLVM struct type
           definitions, global variables, string constants, and runtime
           function declarations.
  Pass 3 — generateClass() + generateFunction(): emit IR for class methods
           (BEFORE top-level functions, so registerStructMethod runs before
           main's type resolution) and then top-level function bodies.

Output is LLVM IR in SSA form with strictly ascending register numbers
(%1, %2, %3, ...). Each function resets the register counter. Block labels
accumulate across functions within a module for unique loop metadata IDs.

In multi-module mode (generateSingle), one .ll file is produced per source
module. Cross-module references use `declare` stubs built during Pass 1.
Fork-parallel generation compiles uncached modules in child processes with
CoW memory snapshots of the registry state.

Key data structures:
  - varNames[]/varRegs[]/varTypes[]: parallel arrays tracking in-scope
    variables, their alloca registers, and Seen types. Searched backwards
    so inner scopes shadow outer ones.
  - structFieldNames[]/structFieldTypes[]/structLayouts[]: parallel arrays
    for struct layout registry (field names are comma-separated, field
    types are pipe-separated).
  - g_cseKeysArr/g_cseValsArr: CSE (Common Subexpression Elimination)
    cache mapping expression keys to register names. Searched backwards
    for most-recent-scope-first semantics.
///

